hap 10 Exercise :

NAME and EXPLANATION
Shell
 command-line interpreter or shell that provides a command line user interface for Unix-like operating systems 

Option
special kind of argument that modifies the effects of a command 

Standard output
default file descriptor where a process can write output 

pipe
mechanism for inter-process communication using message passing 

metacharacter
 a character that has a special meaning during pattern processing 

Background process
 executes independently of the shell, leaving the terminal free for other work 

PID
number used by most operating system kernels to uniquely identify an active process. 

program
The code the user write

argument

Parameters for command

Grave accent
will start another shell prompt 

tee
reads standard input, then writes the output of a program to standard output and simultaneously copies it into the specified file or files 

wildcard
symbols or special characters that represent other characters 

Foreground process
processing that supports interaction between interactive and batch operations 

Job number
background processes that are currently running under your shell 

process
process is started when a program is initiated 

Standard input
an input stream where data is sent to and read by a program 

redirection
a form of interprocess communication 

filter
programs that take plain text as standard input, transforms it into a meaningful format, and then returns it as standard output 

quote
used to remove the special meaning of certain characters or words to the shell 

Process id number
 Same as PID

Job control
 ability to selectively stop (suspend) the execution of processes and continue (resume) their execution at a later point 

